name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
An amazing and beautiful library! It's a peaceful getaway right in the middle of the busy city centre. The library is very large, features lots of different facilities and has a peaceful, bright and modern atmosphere. It is definitely worth visiting, even if it's only to sit down for bit, admire the architecture and take in the friendly and peaceful atmosphere.

The top floor most resembles a library in the classic sense with lots of books, places to relax and read, as well as a little cafe. It also has an outdoor terrace with views over the city and the parliament house. On the other floors you will find various facilities such as 3d printers, musical instruments, meeting rooms, game rooms, sewing machines, etc. as well as some quiet nooks and corners. The library is located at walking distance from the central station and is easily accessible.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: An awesome library in Helsinki! Not only the design of the building but also the multitude of things you can learn do here, besides reading. They have instruments, 3D printers, sewing machines to mention a few opportunities to learn to make things with your hands. Very impressive! Beautiful spaces and friendly people!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
This is a beautiful library! Beautifully designed and built.  It’s bright, spacious and a place where one will want to spend all their time.

There is something for every member of the community.

- Sound proof game rooms with large wide-screens and comfy sofas. ✅
- 3D laser printers ✅
- cafe/restaurant with delicious food and drinks ✅
- spacious work areas with sewing machines and supplies for craft activities ✅
- private meeting rooms, sound proof recording studios, musical instruments available for borrowing ✅
- well-lit comfortable spaces to enjoy a good book

There is so much here. And all in a beautiful space.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Just a glorious public space. The best library I've ever been in. Amazing architecture, lovely places to sit and chill, or work, or read, or eat. Highly recommended.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
This library is a very pleasant place where the whole family can come and enjoy activities like playing games, printing, sewing, playing instruments, singing, and more.
Just a short distance from Helsinki's train station. A café is located on the third floor, takes in the sunshine and refreshments in the center of Helsinki.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Wonderful inspiring place to relax, learn, socialize, be creative, broaden horizons and feel completely at home! I wish we could have such a place in Greece and admire the Finnish for their ideals of equity, appreciation to diversity, respect to all citizens and culture.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Amazing place. Modern library in beautiful building. Many spaces to learn, and do some classes, play games, have specific lesson. Nice view point from the terrace.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Lots of people come here just to see the building. Very lively crowded place. Stunning architecture from inside out.
If you are visiting Helsinki - I recommend this place as number one.
Wheelchair friendly, youth friendly, children will love it, great for students and also couples.
Cafe can be found downstairs and upstairs, elevators, escalators, 3D printers, game rooms, music studio, group rooms.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: One of my favorite spots to work from in Helsinki. They have anything and everything from sewing machines to laser cutters to music studios to -of course- books. It's a wonderful piece of architecture and it always brings me joy to visit and spend time.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Oodi, the crown jewel of Helsinki's libraries, is not just a place for bookworms but a buzzing hub of creativity and Nordic architectural charm. With its glass and steel structure topped with a wooden hat, it's like the lovechild of a greenhouse and a Viking longhouse! Inside, you'll find more than just books; there's a smorgasbord of gadgets and gizmos, from sewing machines to 3D printers, making it the perfect spot for both the crafty and the tech-savvy.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: I love this library.  The vibe is really chill but everyone can still find their place here.  You can choose to read or play boardgame here.  Kids may have their own reading or playing space without affecting others.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Excellent! Must visit if you are in Helsinki, however the staff in the cafe upstairs (not library staff but rather some franchise) are awfully rude and unhelpful. The cold drinks come hot the hot drinks come cold, They don't clean anything properly either. I would advise you to avoid the place altogether and bring your own food and drinks

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Unexpectedly organic architecture, inspiringly inviting to create. A bit too many weirdos, street people sleeping in the second floor, maybe there should be an entrance for hygiene check. Third floor full of kids the space keeps you the feeling of being outdoor not inside or separate from the surrounding.. spectacular architecture..

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Beautifully designed library with lots of amenities for use on a reserve-basis. Including music instruments, recording studios, video game rooms, 3D printers, chess tables and sewing machines. Super cool!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Was really impressive to see this library, the design, the people there, and the thoughtful touches.

It has a young feel and energy to it, with many teens coming here to study, do homework or just play a game. The architecture of the library is beautifully Nordic.

One of my favorite places in Helsinki.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Visiting the Helsinki Central Library Oodi was an absolute pleasure! From the moment we stepped inside, we were captivated by the modern architecture and open spaces of this modern, ship-shaped building. The ground floor is home to a lovely cafeteria with affordable food, which proved to be a great place for a relaxing break.

The middle mezzanine is a hub of creativity and collaboration, equipped with an impressive range of facilities including 3D printers, laser engraving printers, ironing boards, sewing stations and much more. Adjacent are well-equipped music studios, Playstation dens and meeting rooms, all buzzing with people working on different projects - meeting, discussing, socialising and creating.

The top floor is the icing on the cake - a large open space, beautifully laid out and well lit, housing an extensive collection of books. We spent relaxing hours exploring this level, admiring not only the books but also the phenomenal design and thoughtful arrangement of designated reading and contemplation areas with a wonderful variety of chairs, armchairs and sofas to curl up in and get lost in a book or other work. There was also a designated area for toddler play and plenty of space to park strollers.

One small suggestion for improvement would be to expand the information about the building on the library's website. A more detailed exploration of the architecture, design themes and history of the competition for the building could enrich the experience for curious visitors like us.

Despite this minor quibble, we left Oodi with a deep appreciation for this incredible public space that fosters creativity and community. The people of Helsinki can be proud to have such a wonderful resource at their doorstep.

We are grateful for an unforgettable morning at Oodi and look forward to returning in the future. Hats off to the people of this vibrant city!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Beautiful library located in Helsinki. Everyone can go inside. It is a space where adults, children, youth, and the elderly can all come together.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Too bad I can’t give 10 ⭐️ Oodi would deserve it! Such a beautiful space with so many activities- sewing, printing, 3d printing, recording, playing instruments 🤗 Also the space for kids is just precious. I really enjoyed visiting.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Absolutely loved it. It's huge! You can do your reading, do your work, read while eating, get own private place or read outside. Relaxed and comfy ambience. Lots of books, visual materials and many media forms to choose from.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
This is probably my favorite place in Helsinki.
You can do a lot of things here.
Unbelievable!
They have small cabins where you can have some privacy in case you have a meeting either online or face to face.
You can photocopy documents.
There’s fast internet.
You can rent books.
You can charge your phone or laptop or any gadgets for that matter.
There are plenty of space for you to read, surf the net, or just do whatever you wish with your time.
The staff are friendly!
Toilets are clean.
There’s a cafe in case you wish to eat.
Perfect place!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Beautiful library in the heart of Helsinki. It's free and has a great collection of works. There are also cute little robots that bring out books to you! Fascinating place. The modern architecture is the building is gorgeous.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: What a architectural beauty of a multifunctional library, symbolizing a lot of the Finnish values. Realy enjoyed visiting it!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Helsinki Central Library Oodi is a fantastic modern library in the heart of Helsinki. The architecture is stunning, and the staff are welcoming and helpful. There are game station playing room, printing services, cafe and restaurant. The building serve more than the traditional library we expected.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: An amazing structure. It offers millions of services and stands as an iconic symbol of the 21st century, distinctly different from the surrounding buildings that were constructed in earlier years.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Crazy, what a blast. I Wish we would have such an Open Center of creativity in Germany, Open space, great Things to do, modern space, great for Young people. Wow

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Love the Oodi Helsinki so much! The building is very eye-catching with contemporary and modern curves outside
And the interiors inside also very comfortable sophisticated and functional at the same time
Makes you comfortable to read the book at any corner 😊 📖

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
One of the best libraries I've seen. They have a lot of stuff for makers like 3D printers, recording studios, electronics labs, sewing machines and plenty or working spaces.
Be careful with your belongings there are thieves operating inside, I got robbed but luckily the thieves were caught by cameras and after reporting to the police they found them and I could get back my travelling backpack.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Overall the Library is lovely, you can experience various different things here at quite reasonable cost. It has a chess play area, video games, and kids play area. This is the best, I have seen for the first time in the Library where kids play.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Great, modern library in the heart of Helsinki not far from the central station. The offer is extraordinary: the building has three floors. Upstairs there is a large book collection and workstations. The WLAN is free of charge. Toilets are also available. On the second floor there are workstations and group rooms, a film studio and sound studios that can be rented. There is also a large kitchen that can be booked. 3D printers, sewing machines and plotters are also available. There is a large reception area downstairs. Visitors can play chess here, for example.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: I have never seen such a wonderful library in my entire life. The place is huge, with different levels where you can play chess, book for a study room, play music a studio, learn how to sew, read a book on your own, play video games, … I was so amazed how this place is. This is an example for the entire world. I loved it !

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
I'm so impressed of this building in terms of architectural design and variety of functions.
There are many functions except being just library. Workshops, flexiable working spces, private rooms for study or meeting, game rooms etc.
Upper floor with flooting, wavy ceiling with roof windows and trees create very natural and organic inner space.
Definately worth to visit, even spend time reading or writing...

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: A really beautiful modern library with lots of different things that can be borrowed, used or rented. They have rentable cubicles for studying, gaming, meetings and more and also rentable studios. They have 3D printers and other types of printers / equipment that can be used (for a (small) fee). They have a cafe and they even have a play area for kids. There are robots which can put back books into the shelves for you. And there are elevators and escalators throughout the building. I think this library is equipped for everything you could possibly need of it! I would definitely recommend coming here!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Very interesting place! You can read, relax, eat, listen music, create! must to do in Helsingin!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Need to take a meeting? Want to print that part for your project? Have some downtime to play the latest Xbox game? Forgot that book?

You can do that all here.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Wow, what a brilliant library with so many things to do from computer games to playing chess or even just chill. Toilets were clean. The Helsinki sign is next to the building and can be seen from the first floor window where the chess area is.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Coolest library I’ve ever visited. Very impressive. Worth a visit if you’re in Helsinki. Grab a meal at the cafeteria, authentic Finnish food and cheap 13 euros all you can eat. There is a cafe on top floor with good options and food. There are even 3D printers to use with small cost for materials only.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Visited in noon and was quite populated. Helpful staff. A great inclusive space also for tourists to kill time. It is also available to view the city from the 3rd floor balcony

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Quite possibly the best modern library in the world. Don't overlook when in Helsinki.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: More than a library. It offers a living space to anyone in the city even you are just a tourist who needs taking breaks.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
An ode to one of the best library I've visited!
Oodi simply has it all: beautiful architectural building, a restaurant, a cafe, a kid's play area with multiple free animations, a second floor where you can book a working space, 3D or A1 printers, instruments, recording studios, game consoles, anything you think of, even a kitchen!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
The library is beautiful and looks like a calm place to come study.
I recommend you to get a coffee on the terrace on the last floor and enjoy the sun (if he’s there).

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Wow. This place is an absolute gem. A beautiful modern building near a lake with floors of books, musical instruments, 3D printers, newspapers, a cafe, a restaurant, a play area for children and much more. Every city should have a place like this to act as a community hub and cathedral of knowledge and stunning architecture.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: The most amazing modern library from exterior to interior.. loved how it is open for public and how it has other things beside books as well.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
This library is absolutely stunning.
There are so many public spaces and different machines that can be reserved by anyone.
There are studios, learning spaces, workshops and classrooms are only some of what is available.

On a separate note it would be amazing to see this kind of space available in a lot more places and countries.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: What a wondrous place for book lovers! It’s more than a library- people read newspapers, kids climb structures, professionals discuss ideas and others just hangout. Residents of Helsinki are lucky to have this treasure.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Such a wonderful library where you can play chess, book for a study room, play music a studio, learn how to sew, read a book on your own, play video games.& Helpful staff.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
What is there to say about this place ? Is it possible the most unique library I have ever seen in my life ? Yeah, without a doubt.

The amount of things you can do here are truly impressive. Not to mention that they are basically free with how cheap they are. Things you would need costly maschines to do are available to you here publicly. For anyone following a creative hobby, this place is indeed a must see and mist do while in Helsinki.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Such a lovely building - the coolest library in the world in my view! I also recommend the cafe - it has a lovely view of the square beneath it.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Even if you’re only in Helsinki for a day - make Oodi one of your must sees! I was so impressed by everything I saw there. The most magnificent library I have ever visited.

There are - 3D printers, vinyl printers, textile areas, a MOVIE, theater, cafes and restaurants, board game rentals and so much more.

Experiencing Oodi was the highlight of my trip to Helsinki.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: There shouldn’t be guided tours for tourist groups inside the library, in my opinion. It gets crowded and noisy so not many spaces to sit and read in peace.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: LOVE the space. sooooo nice and cozy and creative. Thank you for sharing this with the world.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Truly a one of a kind experience. This library is so much more than just a library. Of course the book selection and reading section is amazing, but that is just the tip of the iceberg. You can find board games, you can rent music instruments, rent an editing studio or recording studio, use 3D printers, laser cutters, try your luck at sowing or crafts, print giant posters and banners, or even play video games on the latest gen consoles (yes, PS5 too), or even PS VR. I have never seen such an amazing library before. I am just heartbroken that I can’t take advantage of most of this stuff because I am not a resident of Helsinki. But that doesn’t matter, you MUST go there, it is definitely an eye-opening experience. The atmosphere is amazing too, especially during the winter, the library becomes a hub for everyone.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Just spent the afternoon at the Odii Library in Helsinki, and it’s such a hidden gem! Whether you're a bookworm or just looking for a quiet escape in the city, this place has everything you need.

✨ The reading spaces are so comfortable, with soft chairs and natural light streaming through the windows.

📖 From fiction to non-fiction, they have something for everyone, including books in multiple languages.

☕ I grabbed a coffee and spent hours reading—it’s honestly the perfect spot to unwind and disconnect for a while.

If you’re ever in Helsinki, definitely make time to stop by Odii Library. It’s more than just a place for books; it’s an experience!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: What a beautiful and unique library. Architecture is amazing but the actual library is super cool. Lots of facilities. You can collaborate and study and do lot's of educational work here. A model for rest of the world's libraries

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
This is definitely not the library you are looking for....

It's a lot more than that! Quite impressive 👍 Good job Finns 🇫🇮 !

At its core it's indeed a library, you can visit freely, rent a book, read it and enjoy it. But that's only a small portion of things that you can do here.

I found just a few, but I believe you can:
- practice your musical skills but renting a guitar🎸
- get your friends together and record an album 🎙️. Yes there is a full blown studio!
- of you like to build something with your hands, then give it a go. There is an area and equipment that allows you to build something out of wood or even rent a 3d printer!
- want to chill? There are rooms full of gaming consoles, just pick your favorite game 🎮

I probably missed something for sure, but I leave the exploration up to you!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
This is so much more than a library. It's a library reinvented. It's a meeting place, a co-working space, a studio, a workshop, a place for children, a place to relax, a place to have a coffee outside or play chess.

I was blown away by the services available : from a sewing machine, to a 3d printer not to mention the studios to record music. In any other country, you'd never find these together in the same place.

I just love the values of equality and justice that the library brings about. One feels home. I just wish we had this in Paris ! This model ought to be exported

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Amazing gift for Helsinki. The best libary in Finland. It is not the usual, lets be quiet in libary. There are rooms and locations for that. Loved seeing how people were relaxing here. Lovely place, and I met the robot veera. Amazing job and was very interesting how the robots move between the floors by ordering the elevators by themselfs!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Various levels and sections to help resources being channelised.
Escalators help easy access.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Very nice place, you can come with the whole family, you can play, print, sew, play sound instruments, sing and theres more this library can offer for the whole family.
Very accessible also. Near from the train station of Helsinki. There is also a cafe on the 3rd floor. Just remember to have reservations first on other services they offer. Visit the website and you will know more.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: It is a beautiful library, very comfortable. It has 3 floors, on the last floor you can directly choose books in several languages - Finnish, Swedish, German, English. There is also a small selection of books in other languages as well. On the first floor there is access to printing, there is also a sewing machine, games machines and so on.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: The best library I have visited so far! The vibe was different and you cannot imagine that this place is a library. You can utilize many spaces to reshape your skill, not only reading books. You can have fun activities with your friends and family members. There are a 3D printing place, VR, games, and many things. One place that is worth visiting in Helsinki!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
One of the most impressive libraries I've ever visited, it's clear why it's won several awards over the years. There are 3 distinct floors each with a unique purpose - from creating / building, relaxing and gathering, and of course, reading. There's a cafe area on the first floor as well for fresh food and drinks.

Don't miss the robotic "helpers" on the reading floor!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Wonderful place to visit for fun and peace of mind.
The architecture and interior design is amazing.
The library have sound-proof rooms for study & office work, and game rooms for fun.
Rooms can be reserved after getting a library card(Finnish ID is needed to get one).

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: really cool place with plenty to do inside and outside! lovely terrace

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: I have never been more impressed with a government building. Beautiful design with the intent of lending books and everything else you can think of for the people.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Oodi is much more than a library. It is full of life.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Stunning building from the outside. Inside is an absolute Joy to just walk through.  Lots of people working and studying. Highly recommend a visit.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: I love the concept of this library.  Free and enjoyable space that is open to everyone regardless of age and background.   Children are having so much fun here.  Library is no longer a place where you have to behave in orthodox and strict ways.  When I was growing up in the other side of the world, I was not allowed to make any noise in the library as it was supposed to be a place to study or to read.  So, the library for me was an extremely boring place.  But in this beautiful Oodi, you can freely enjoy the library in different ways.   Children here are so fortunate to enjoy this kind of free spirit library.  Well done to Oodi.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: A library that challenges the very typology of library itself. The extensive programs and services offered turn it into a community learning centre or sort, where one can learn to make clothings, 3D print own products, make music, play chess etc. Children spaces on the upper floor becomes a playscape shaped by its flowing architecture and interior, and with different kinds of story-telling spaces for parents to interact with their kids. Family-friendly to its best as evident in the stroller park. Cafes add to the overall social vibe. The use of timber in large curvature reflects the ship-building technique in the past, very apt for its cultural context.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: A public library with a very unique design and offers many different unique services such as 3D printing and laser engraving for users. It's a good place to sit around and read or study. There's an outdoor area at the top floor which offers a good view to the surrounding.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: My favorite piece of architecture, inside and out, in Finland.  Every wall, shelf, bench, reading area is stunning.  Interesting info about Finland and literacy posted along the way.  Make sure you find the beautiful outdoor reading deck.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Helsinki city centre library Oodi is a lively meeting place on Kansalaistori, right in the heart of Helsinki.  Oodi is one of the 38 offices of the Helsinki City Library and part of the Helmet library network.
Oodi complements the cultural and media centre formed by the Music Centre, Finlandia House, Sanomatalo and Kiasma, the Museum of Contemporary Art.  It offers a non-commercial public urban space open to everyone right across from the House of Parliament.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Someone might say a library it’s not really a touristic attraction but this one is the exception. It did WOW me, I’ve got so impressed! The architecture is simply amazing but also the whole concept of a library. My second favourite place in Helsinki after the island. It’s a very must place to visit.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Amazing place to share with friends ideas, creativity, entertainment or quiet seat and read. And everything for free.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: It's a very modern, state-of-the-art library.  It has lots to offer but too little time, especially if you are in the city for just a limited time. There is an interactive room, different sitting areas for your convenience, there's indoor and outdoor, among other things. I would love to come back here again given more time to explore the city. Visiting the library is a MUST when you are in Helsinki.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Probably our favorite building in Helsinki: what a wonderful place.
Sets a standard for how every library should be like.
A great feeling of openness on the top floor and being able to sit outside to read is simply wonderful.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: A huge library, Oodi Helsinki Central Library, has recently opened in the very center of Helsinki. It was recognized as the best new library in the world. Almost €100 million was allocated for its creation. This is a charming space where you can not only take something to read, but also just relax while admiring its alien design.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Helsinki has invested wisely to its quality of life in creating this.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Used to be libraries are quiet places for studying and research but Oodi is anything but these. These are chess games being played onthe ground floor and at least 3 cafes. Second storey is like an open amphitheatre for studing and discussions. The general design of the building is very curvaceous....sexy.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: The most stunning library I’ve ever encountered. Beautifully designed with many amenities including ample seating areas, cafés, work stations, and more.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Very interesting concept and pretty honorable. Make for an interesting shortish visit or a nice working session - that is outside tourists times! Otherwise get quite hectic and free spaces get rare.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: One of the best libraries I've ever been too. Great views from the upper floor, you can enjoy the sunset while reading a nice book. Also they have the middle floor for students to do brainstorming & mix together with all kinds of technology devices. I'll be back next time maybe even this afternoon. Lastly the entire building from the outside looks like the DNA Double Helix 10/10

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: This is a MUST SEE when you are in Helsinki, even Finland. A visit to the will transport you to a futuristic experience that will DEFINITELY have an impact on yourself.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: The library is great. The location is good, and the library is really fresh. There is spaces for everyone whether you want to study, have a meeting or just play some games with friends. Definitely recommend. I have personally been there on weekends and you can really focus in the silent rooms.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: The word " library" does not come close to describing the multiplicity of functions, services, and roles that this space fulfills. On the one hand, there are plenty of books, magazines, and journals as one can expect. However, on the other hand, there are spaces for playing board games,  video games, organizing in-person and hybrid events and meetings, spaces to practice music, playrooms for kids, as well as cafés and restaurants to sustain the body and not just one's curiosity. Certainly, this is a must place to visit when you are in town.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Probably the most impressive library I have seen to date. Kudos to the Finns.

It has a wide range of literature and art objects (dog sculpture!) on display.

An impressive staircase, an inclusive physical map of the place (including Braille language), everything from kids' literature, comics to magazines, and conventional reads.

What also stuck out: like many shops and NGOs in Finland, staff wore LGBTIQ+ keychains. :) Much appreciated!

I used it to charge my Mac and phone, check out the Star Wars comics, and have a snack in between appointments.

They have a cafe on the first floor, and also what looks like a restaurant downstairs, which at the time looked closed.

Lots of LED lights, and what also transpired.. it is an inclusive, appreciative place, with lots of kids (different cultures) playing freely.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: It's the best library I've ever been to! There's free access to everyone. Here, you'll find sewing machines, 3D printers, a recording studio, playstation rooms and cafes and restaurants. they have vegan and gluten free options. There's also an area for children to play. It's like a little city inside Helsinki. Definitely recommend checking it out if you're visiting.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: This is the insanest building and offer I have ever seen a country make for their citizens. Apart frol the crazy architecture which is honestly a huge flex, inside there are SO many things, all, FREE for the people. Incredible

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Very nice place! The library is not only place for self-education, but for time-spending! There's kindergarten, 3D printers, irons, music recording studio, co-working space, etc. The most impressive is robots, who are accepting books instead of librarians.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Very nice atmosphere, large, can get crowded in weekends, lots of tourists but lots of seats to read and work. With cafe inside. Books are mostly in Finnish. The third floor is very open, the vibes are good, different type of seats with nice view

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Wonderful place to visit. Free entry.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: This is what the future of libraries should be. What a beautiful, modern library! Complete with a space for makers and co-working. We saw people sewing, 3D printing and more. Wide open space that is clean with beautiful architecture. The cafes have lovely sandwiches and pastries. The bathroom was a massive coed space with touch free sinks. If you’re visiting Helsinki, definitely come here!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Truly fantastic new central library! This building is a treat on itself, not to mention the outstanding set-up where the books in various languages (mainly Finnish, Swedish and English) are treated equally -- rather than being separated in different sections of the building.

Plenty of nice hidden nooks for sitting down and enjoying browsing a magazine, making a start of reading a new book, or simply observing the hustle and bustle of the city.

Lots of creative ideas for updating the role of libraries in the modern society, including maker's spaces, lending much more than just books and good IT resources.

This truly is a library for everyone!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: So beautiful and nice design, inside and outside. Love how there is play spaces for kids! Nice toilets also.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Perfect place to learn, study and play! You never can see something like this all around the Europe!
Guess what! They have robots the help people to bring right book for them and is a perfect place for any kind of artists to practice on their project!
They have meetings room, recording studio for musicians, high quality and extra large printers with high resolution monitors for photographers and graphic designers! I think this is the best place to develop yourself to be better person!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Spectacular architecture and an accidental tourist attraction. The structure of the Helsinki Central Library Oodi is amazing. From the front, it looks like a kool and sleek ship and from the side, it is a beautiful art piece. The top floor which houses the books also functions an open reading area sloping upwards on the two ends. Gorgeous!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
No mistake this is a lovely family friendly space for people to visit and enjoy the environment surrounding libraries. Interactive stations for sewing,  making things (3d printers, design spaces, etc), local cinema, restaurant, accessible toilets, and much more. In case reading needs inspiration, there are great views from the main (top) floor of books.
It is a few minutes from the central train station, and lots of accessible features. Staff are helpful and speak Finnish, Swedish and English very well. Toilets are unisex, but small cubicles. Accessible toilets use the modern 'active' symbol for disabilities. Congrats Helsinki for making the library a great place to visit.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
You come here as an ordinary (western) European or American and you are stunned by the public cultural service that is provided.
Definitely check out the gaming area on the 1st floor. They have a PC Pool, console area including PS5 and VR, Audio Studios, I couldn't believe it. Seems like progressive, reformed democratic welfare systems are working quite good. :D

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Absolutely amazing building - both aesthetically and functionally. It’s a public library that is open and accessible for everyone. You don’t need a library card to get in, but it is needed if you want to use some of the facilities.

On the second floor there is a maker space, sewing machines, big plotters and printers, game rooms, and a lot of space to hang out, study or work.

The library is on the third very spacious and light filled floor. On the on side of it you have space for small kids and on the other area where you can work and concentrate.

Great example of what a public library/space should be! So well thought through, warm, welcoming and full of activities and people.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Awesome awesome awesome
Beautiful designed looks odd exterior but once u step in it’s a haven
No wonder Finnish people are the happiest in the world

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: I do not have a good impression of Helsinki until I have visited this library. Everything is so expensive in Helsinki and you even need to pay for using the toilet in Central Station, Finland is a very high tax country and the Government doesn’t even provide basic services like free toilet in public transport venues. Don’t talk about freedom when you have no freedom to pee. That is shameless! So coming to this fabulous library at least let you know where the government spent the taxpayers’ money at.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: A truly open public space for all. Beautiful facilities. Its near to the Holiday Inn hotel, the Parliament & museum of fine arts. It's the day after Finland beat Canada at Ice Hockey - so there's gonna be a big celebration here tonight

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Highly recommended! Very modern and well equipped. You can study, work, or even record music! A modern building and also a place for people to come together.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: What an amazing architecturally designed library. Not only the structure, the concept of learning methods and learning space have simply blown my mind away. I wish we have this kind of learning environment in our country. There are spaces for 3D design, print, virtual reality .... just to name a few. Simply wow!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Lovely place to stay for every occasion/intention, great place to feel at peace. Been here a lot through the year and I love it

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: This could well be the best building in the world. It is a fantastic library that seeks to share knowledge with a different approach. The building itself is incredible. However, the best part is the inside. There's three floors full of unique spaces for everyone to learn. From music & video studios, to 3D printers, to chess boards, to children's playgrounds, to books, to conference rooms and places to collaborate. I read a review say that other countries should visit to understand how to invest their education funds and I couldn't agree more.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: This is an architectural wonder and certainly not just a library. I cannot be but envious of those living in Helsinki having such an incredible facility at their doorstep.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Simply amazing place. No access limits, 3D printers, recording studios, great architecture, board games, computer games. And naturally full of books, many of them in English. Tax money well spent.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: I have never seen a Library of this kind before. Huge space full of life! People everywhere enjoy every bit of space. 3d printers, game rooms, computer spaces, study rooms and loads of books, simply anything you could ask for in a library!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: This is fine public place - you can walk in - read, work, jut sit around. Many moms with children, but not messy :). Stunning architecture and interior. This place tells something about the Finns and their mentality. Go and see.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: It is a great architecture and a wonderful place. Individual and group study rooms, reading rooms, labs and so on. Perfect place.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Did you know a "Library" equipped with not just books but every utility which you, your kid, fashion student, coder, architect...basically anybody needs, this place has it all.
It is a go to place for everybody (ironic right, but it's true).
If you enter, you wouldn't want to leave.
This place is beyond explanation.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Amazing structure, a really incredible library everything is free. So many materials even board games. The space is large and full of many possibilities to learn many different things and take part of many different courses. Very nice area to work on your own projects. Very nice staff ☺️ as well.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Best library in the world. For families with kids it's like a day off or going to the amusement park.

It has everything for everyone.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Absolutely futuristic design. This building attracts the attention of any person. The multi-million dollar library features not only books but 3D printers, recording studios, gaming rooms, a small cinema, and other leisure facilities. Free to visit.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
The most fascinating place to visit in Helsinki (apart from saunas)

This library should be the acclaimed standard for other  countries as a show case how invested money into education and services can benefit everyone in the city. Not to mention it's good for tourism too.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Amazing architecture and a great space of you have children. We also had some coffee and local snacks at the cafe inside the library. It was very busy but and everyone looked amazed on how it was build. It's a very big building with a lot to see and do.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Great library, not only the place to read a book, but also the place to do many things like play a game, do several workshops, and be a co-working space.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Finally managed to visit Helsinki's Oodi Library (voted Best Library in the World). Here, besides books, there are also photography studios to hire, large format printing, gaming rooms, music studios, Lazer printing and 3d printing facilities, just to mention a few. Oh, and it also looks spectacular.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Modern and state of the art library. I thoroughly enjoyed visiting the library.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Oodi library or the central library located just adjacent to the Helsinki central railway station. This central library is an excellent place for students, emerging entrepreneurs other than regular library goers because this place has special video conference and team work meeting rooms which can be accessed by the emerging entrepreneurs and facilities like a hall with internet facility are good place for students and other leisure places to sit and read books and learning like stitching, 3D printing and game area including play stations for relaxing .. an absolute combo for social goers ! Never ever miss to visit this library !

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Why sit alone inside, when you can hang in the neat athmospheare with the neat people? Oodi is not just an amazing library, it is a meeting/working/creating/playing venue for everybody. It is open every day, late in the evening. Just watching the people there is enough. Oodi is living in the future now.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
New Helsinki central library "Oodi", latest addition to Helsinki city 37 libraries.

Great place to hangaround, having inspirational vibe.

Collection includes 140000 items and estimated annual visitor count is 2 million people. Total cost was 100 million Euros.

Has a bistro, movie theatre, 3D- and large format printers, gaming-, computer- and VR rooms, quiet rooms, loanable global magazines, newspapers, movies, - and books.

Open for every soul.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: The central library is a modern concept that is child-friendly. Unlike most libraries, this one is designed to resemble homes living room and children do not need to be quiet. It's a welcoming environment for the whole family. The idea is really neat and the design is very cool.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Amazing place to spent some time alone with books or doing great things with friends. Also architecture of this place is amazing! One of the best spots in Helsinki.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: I was here more like a tourist. My phone was dead and I wanted to have a snack. It is an amazing place. You can chill, study, work and practice your creativity here. I've never met such libraries before. People come here with their families. The only thing if you need some quiet place then it is better to go another library. But in Helsinki it is not a problem.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Great library in Center of Helsinki. Recomendation to take payed guid3 (124eur), lady Will show you and explain all important points and give informations about idea, planing, building and running od 4he library. They have a robot to collectin g books!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: I spent my last evening in Helsinki at the Oodi library . It loved the atmosphere . The timings are quite generous and the decor and seating area is lovely.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: One of the main attraction in Helsinki, Master class example of Architecture. Amazing design. Very thoughtful of designer. Must visit in Helsinki the location walking distance from center.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Places like these and a very planned concept for social places like these make Finland stand out in terms of well balanced life. The architecture itself is unique and amazing apart from the concept. You come here to read, study, work, sew, craft, childrens play in as a group or family or alone.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Such a great space, right in the middle of Helsinki.  I had the pleasure of visiting it just few months after the opening. Full of books and places to relax, have a coffee while reading them. Also an entire floor for booking meeting rooms.

I noticed their cleaners must be shorter than me, since the bookshelves are full of dust on the top :)

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: The library is so nice, it's have anything what u need to do your project

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: This modern, unique place is more than just a librirary. It is taking the word “library” to completely another level.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
A bit otherworldly from a touristic experience. Worth coming back to. Or moving to Finland altogether.

A bike rental station next to it could be a nice addition.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: one of my favourite places in helsinki! there’s a lot free options to spend time with and every worker is polite and nice they help every time when i needed this

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: National Central Library. One of the most beautiful building in Helsinki and one of the most effective library. Many facilities, including 3d printer, etc. Kids corner. Very interesting the European Union Corner. Beautiful coffee shop.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
We walked there to meet my husband who was working in one of the work rooms. We took a break together at the Kiosk on the 3rd floor. It's a clean, calm environment that's both welcoming & inspirational.
One of the nicest libraries I've seen.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Another level. This is the gift Finland gave to their citizens on the occasion of 100th anniversary of independence. Voted by Finns as their preferred choice. Think about it. What would your countrymen have chosen? What would your country have proposed? A stadium? A statue?
Deeply impressed with the civic values of this country.
Once you enter, apart from the obvious mind boggling architecture, books galore, autonomous robotic book carriers, etc there’s a Urban workshop with free facilities and state of the art equipment (3D printers, pro grade sound, photo and video studios, VR and Xbox/PS4/… boxes, meeting rooms, even sewing equipment).
Talk about “put your money where your mouth is” for creative fostering. Well done Finland.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: This place is fantastic! It's easily one of the most modern and impressive libraries around. There's so much to do here. You can even book private rooms for free! They've got everything from sound studios to photography studios, music rooms, a biography section, a coffee shop, a lunch restaurant, and of course, tons of books. Plus, it's conveniently located in the heart of the city, making it easily accessible via local traffic.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: A beautiful library, so spacious and modern with lot of amenities. A must visit

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Such an impressive building and the offered equipment is so modern and actually used by loads of young people. Would love to have something similar in my hometown.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Amazing library, both inside as outside architecture is stunning. At night the wave outside has lights to enhance the feeling of the curved roof.

From inside you can go to the upper floor and have an amazing view (both inside as outside and drink a coffee.

Besides the building itself you have many books you can rent, but it definitely is a more innovative library with flexible rooms for studying. 3D printing. And many more.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: A library put of this world. A nice Cafe inside and a place for everybody to enjoy away from the cold weather outside.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Such a beautiful library! You really have a lot to do ant the staff is really nice too ☺️

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: This modern library has just about everything to make one's day, from books and magazines to chess sets to board games to video game rooms to recording studios. However, the waiting period for the recording studio is around two months.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Ugh!!! I am so jealous they have this nice lovely library. Nice branding, fun furniture, good selection of books... and AMAZING architecture.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: That place is just amazing. Easy to find the book you'd like to read, cozy atmosphere, comfortable chairs. I loved the chairs that faced the window and you could work with your book and enjoy the city view at the same time. Absolutely fell in love with that library. Also there are couple spots to get a coffee and a quick snack while you work.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
An incredible to simply kick back and simply "be" and even learn!
The building is stunning. Worth a visit multiple times over and over and over again

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: One of the most beautiful and functional libraries in the world. It’s not a building, it’s a philosophy, with the space reflecting certain ideals. THIS is living architecture.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Good toilets and board game selection. Also enjoyed a show from Eesa at the balcony, wow!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Incredible! Had some time in the city to walk around - spent some of that checking out the library. It’s truly a gem! If I lived here I would absolutely take greater advantage of the library services. Even just passing through, having some espresso and snacks on the rooftop with a view was great. Seeing the architecture and walking through the library was incredibly enjoyable.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Amazing tranquil place. Great architecture. Awesome place to browse books or just hang.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Amazing. The most beautiful library we ever seen.
Very special building with a lot of wood.
You can do everything you want there.
There are gaming rooms. Meeting places. Sawing machines. 3 d printers and books and music instruments.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Beautiful and open for everyone. A place beaming with kindness, creativity and wisdom

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Modern, spacious, definitely an object that should be seen while in Helsinki.
I had never seen anything so impressive before, there was everything - a cafe, virtual reality rooms, offices, an iron, a terrace, a 3D printer, computers, copiers, so many possibilities and the range of books did not go unnoticed.
I saw something like that for the first time in my life, something unreal. A place to relax, unwind, work and enjoy the beautiful view from the terrace. Also, it is near the center. 😍

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Absolutely an example of a library that is very nice, friendly, modern, giving Access to information for everyone.

Definitely a must see.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Fantastic place for adults and kids alike, plenty to do for all interests and a fun play area on the top floor. Coffee and snacks available

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Nice and comfortable place to rest, read and have some meal brake in the centre of Helsinki. Always visited by me during my trips there.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: For the time of my visit, this place made me feel like I was living in some utopian future, where there are no wars and man and earth live in total harmony

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: An amazing place to visit, read and be creative. The building architecture is wonderful. Plenty of options to meet, work, print on paper, print 3D items, read books in peace, borrow books or borrow games. Staff is always very helpful and polite. Every time is a pleasing experience

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Interesting place to visit as a tourist, to get to know the local environment. With lots of space to work, read or chat

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Good place to come to relax, read, go online. There are small cafes on each floor.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: It will be the perfect place for self-study as nowhere offers such good facilities to learners. The extremely disappointing issue is that the study area is just next the wc rooms and the noises from the opening-closing doors are so loud, iritating and chronical. I think the service can be better much if they can add some soft material among the doors for gently closing... some how. Also no tourists around and take pictures as if we are window-monkeys in their interests...

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: The architecture is wonderful and modern! We loved visiting this place. You have to go to the 3rd floor and enjoy the view outside

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Great location. Very beautiful, lots of exiting things to do and see, and easy to spend an entire day there together with your kids, even if they don't read as much as you'd like them to read.. Far from your ordinary library.

What impressed us too though was the all-you-can-eat lunch buffet. Very tasty and price-wise a good deal, but we liked most the large variety of clearly labelled vegan and gluten-free options, including wheat-free bread. First time for us to enjoy buffet-style food despite having allergies.

Strangely though, the staff did not know the actual ingredients of any dishes, nor did they know the difference between an intolerance or an allergy. Kindly they made some calls for us to ensure items are allergen-free, but a little bit more knowledge would have made us feel safer.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Super cool public library! Marvelous architectural design. Don’t miss it when you’re visiting Helsinki.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: No vinyls here. But it is magnificent as a building. The views from the top are over the Music Hall and the Parliament. As a library it is said packing less books than “a normal” library.  Lots of people just sitting inside, chatting, spending their time. A place where helsinkians (and tourists) likes to just “do nothing”.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
It's great, has everything you need. If you want to study, or do work in peace, you can't find it here. There are either loud children or teens everywhere and you won't be able to find a comfortable and quiet place, since it's always so full. Booking a quiet place is also always filled.

As a public space, it's great. As a classic library where you go read or do work, it's very lacking. There are much better places for this.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: What an amazing place, definitely worth a visit. Loved the architecture and found the different options to work and study fascinating!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Great place to take a break if sightseeing in Helsinki. Lots of places to sit down and admire the view to the parliament house.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Unique design. Beautiful building.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Fantastic multi purpose building for baby, kids and adults to read, play music, build Prototyps or learn

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Beautiful library! There is even a section for stroller parking in the children’s area, and signs that ask for no photos there. There is a “shoeless” section where kids can play without shoes on, also. There are multiple places for a snack/meal and coffee inside. There are elevators and ramps available inside. I loved the beautiful staircase, too. As a mother, this is the perfect library!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
I am amazed how much can be done in a library! It is definitely a place to nurture entrepreneurs and scientists of the future.
More travel photos IG: helenhandicraft

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: On vacations in Helsinki, we decided to visit Oodi- the Helsinki Central library, and I must say this place has changed the concept of a library for us. Library is not books any more. Oodi has urban workspaces, play areas, movie screenings, board games and so much more beyond books. Can keep a family with kids occupied for hours in one go. Also it is equipped with latest 3D printers, engraving facilities, sewing machines and though we didn’t use those, I believe they are available for use to general populace at minimal costs. Absolutely a delightful place ….

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
I live in Sweden but was visiting Helsinki and wanted a place to sit for a couple of hours and do some work on my computer.

The architecture is really breathtaking and the personnel are helpful and cheerful.

I sat in the top floor and all around me it was mostly parents with their kids. I could only appreciate the quality parent-child time that was happening all around me. Some were reading books and some were just engaging in discussions.

Interesting place if you're tired of walking around Helsinki and want to sit down and exercise your brain a bit. They also have some food options in the ground floor but IIRC it had limited options and limited opening times.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Unique wooden, wavey, architecture. A lot of open space

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Nice place with awesome collection of books. Work space, printing , sewing , gaming room , meeting rooms everything makes the place absolutely fantastic. Must visit place for tourists. The library itself is beautiful and the surrounding park also is a good place to spend the evening.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: overcrowded. Not possible to book any meetings rooms at all, except if you book them well in advance. This is because students book rooms for long time every day and many times just to check whatsapp in the phone or just play with youtube videos or twitter pages. This leads into kicking productive meetings (either for students or more often for enterpreneurs and remote digital nomad workers).

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Amazing place. These is first word for everyone

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
2階には、階段に座り読書する場所以外に、3Dプリンターやミシンがあり、何かを製作している大人の？空間。
3階はさらに大きく広い木の階段が左右にあり、そこに自由に座り本を読む人々、カフェ、オープンエアのテーブルもあり。
たくさんの赤ちゃん連れの親子が集い、楽しんでいる様子も伺えました。
本には？ですが、窓が大きく光が入り、明るく気持ちいいです。
ボードゲームまであり。
赤ちゃんスペース脇のトイレは、ジェンダーフリー。
ヘルシンキの一等地、中央駅からすぐ近く。日本でいえば、銀座や東京駅の真ん前に図書館があるような立地。

図書館の固定概念をいい意味で覆されたのは、シンガポールのオーチャードにある図書館以来。
日本の都心にも、ちょっと疲れた時に休憩できるように駅近の図書館があったらなあと切に希望。

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
OODI, la biblioteca centrale della città ed è come entrare nel paese delle meraviglie.
Lasciando la parte la meravigliosa struttura vediamo cosa ci offre.
L’idea di fondo è quella di un polo multifunzionale che la comunità possa frequentare liberamente senza necessariamente voler consultare i libri.
L’edificio, in vetro e acciaio con la facciata in legno, è davvero grande: si estende su tra piani, ognuno con una diversa funzione.
Il piano terra è un vasto spazio polifunzionale: qui c’è il desk dell’accoglienza, spazi dove sedersi e dove giocare a scacchi, un bel ristorante, una sala cinema e un auditorium.
Il primo piano è dedicato al lavoro, allo studio e all’apprendimento e allo stare insieme ad amici e familiari. Qui si può stare comodamente seduti sui alcuni gradoni oppure usufruire delle sale dedicate alla lettura, alle riunioni di lavoro, ai videogiochi: ci sono sale di registrazione,  uno studio fotografico e anche una sala DJ/karaoke!
Si può prenotare anche una cucina attrezzata per fare lezioni di gruppo
A disposizione degli utenti ci sono stampanti 3D, macchine per cucire e ferri da stiro, presse a caldo, taglierine laser.
Al secondo piano, c’è la zona lettura della biblioteca. È un ambiente ampissimo, luminoso grazie alle grandi finestre che si aprono sui lati, che assomiglia vagamente ad una nave dato che alle due estremità lo spazio si assottiglia e il pavimento s’innalza a formare gradoni dove ci si può sedere.
Ampio e’ lo spazio per i bambini.
Completa il tutto un enorme terrazzo.
Io ci ho passato ore invidiando molto chi puo’ usufruirne tutti i giorni.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: La Biblioteca Oodi di Helsinki era uno dei siti da visitare in quanto molto ben recensito e pubblicizzato. Mai mi sarei aspettato un simile spazio per la cittadinanza, che poco ha a che fare con una biblioteca. Anzitutto una struttura moderna e funzionale, poi entrando si scoprono tre piani dove é possibile l'impossibile. Stanze aperte e chiuse per riunioni di tutti i tipi, spazi per cucire, per leggere, studiare, registrare canzoni, per giocare a giochi elettronici, per giocare a scacchi, luoghi di aggregazione per bambini, apparecchi per stampare foto e materiale in 3d, e tanto tanto altro. Ah, dimenticavo, ci sono pure i libri ed il robottino che li riporta a posto. É gratuita. Come si fa a non andarci ?

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
很漂亮的圖書館，
不論是外表還是裡面，
旋轉的樓梯也十分有特色，
這裏算是多功能圖書館，
除了藏書之外，
也有會議室讓人預約開會，
除此之外還有遊戲室，
最令人驚艷的是有幼童去，
許多家長帶小孩來這邊學爬，
十分的可愛，
讓小孩從小在這個環境成長，
很有啟發性。

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Bibliothèque absolument magnifique ! L'architecture est très originale, l'intérieur est très grand, vous pouvez rentrer gratuitement juste pour visiter et vous y balader ou même prendre un verre ! De nombreux espaces de co-working en tout genre sont disponibles (Informatique, réunion, salle de musique...) on peut même jouer à la console de jeux en libre accès ! La salle dédiée aux livres et à la lecture est immense et il y a une terrasse qui est magnifique avec une belle vue la ville. Cette bibliothèque est top pour travailler comme pour se détendre ! En visite à Helsinki, il faut la voir sans faute !

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
7年連続幸福度ランキング第一位のフィンランドの象徴と言ってもいいような公共の図書館。私のような観光客、ペットちゃん、退職して暇そうな年配の方々、小さなお子様、（申し訳ない）浮浪者！？、誰をも受け入れています。
そして、図書館の枠を超えた多くのことができます。エントランスを入ると、すぐ脇にはチェスが何台も置かれていますし、3Dプリンタも自由に使えるようでした。トートバッグの作成（6€）コーナーもあるし、小さなお子様がまるで公園のように遊んでいる場所もありました。
そして、いちいち置かれているものがすべてかっこいい😎これが北欧デザインか？！
食事も摂ることができました。写真のスープランチ（€12ほど）とてもおいしかったです。

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Harika bir yer. Sadece kitap değil, dikiş makinası, 3D printer, oyun odaları, toplantı odaları, sessiz odalar, grup odaları... O kadar harika bir ortam ki hayran kaldık. Çocuklar aileleriyle hem oynuyor hem okuyor, gençler sohbet ve kitaplarla haşır neşir, kimisi balkonda yemek yiyor, kimisi t-shirt baskısı yapıyor, özetle halk bu kütüphaneyi son derece etkin kullanıyor. Burayı görünce neden eğitimde bir numara olduklarını anladım. Mutlaka gelşn ve soluyun bu atmosferi.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Es mucho más que una biblioteca, es un centro cultural abierto a la comunidad y gratuito. Se pueden hacer varias actividades, reservar salas de estudio o de reuniones, estudios de grabación, usar impresoras 3D y máquinas de coser, en fin, de todo.
El edificio es espectacular, tiene hasta una cafetería, y el espacio público alrededor de la biblioteca es usado por jóvenes para bailar o hacer skate. No se lo pierdan

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: 是一座外觀非常美麗令人驚豔的現代化建築，內部空間非常寬廣，閱讀區也非常舒適

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Cumartesi günü oldukça kalabalık oluyor, hafta içi gelmek daha mantıklı olabilir. Kendi broşüründe de belirtildiği gibi alt kat toplantılı etkinlikler, orta kat yaratıcılık, üst kat ise okuma için ideal. Alt katta sinema salonu, restoran ve fotokopi makineleri, orta katta grup ve bireysel çalışma alanları, okuma alanları, müzik odaları, halka açık bilgisayar ve ofset makineleri, 3D yazıcı, ortak kullanılan müzik aletleri, eğitim odaları ve üst katta kitaplar, gazeteler, dergiler ile cafe var. Burayı bir kütüphaneden ziyade bir deneyim ve işbirliği merkezi olarak tanımlamak daha doğru olacaktır. Arkadaşlarla grup çalışması yapmak ve ardından terasta bir kahve içmek için ideal bir mekan.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Библиотеките обикновено не са туристическа цел, но тази в Хелзинки със сигурност е интересно да се види.
Много интересна сграда от архитектурна гледна точка, изненадва посетителите със своята атмосфера.
Заслужава си няколко минути на откритата тераса с изглед към площада пред сградата.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: A Biblioteca Central Oodi é um local único. Para além da arquitetura moderna e impressionante, este edifício oferece uma panóplia de experiências culturais, artísticas, entretenimento e lazer aos seus visitantes. Ler livros é apenas uma das dezenas de experiências que é possível fazer. Jogar jogos, ver filmes, alugar instrumentos musicais, estúdios, salas de conferência, restaurante e até cinema. É incrível e mostra o nível de qualidade de vida que esta cidade oferece.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Rewelacyjne miejsce dla wszystkich od 0 do 100 lat w więcej. Można poczytać, pograć, popracować, spotkać się z innymi, porozmawiać ( nie trzeba być cicho jak w innych bibliotekach). Są też tacy co ucinają sobie drzemkę 😂. Dostępne napoje i drobne przekąski. Są też dźwiękoszczelne boksy, studio nagrań itp. Dla dzieciaczków miejsca do zabawy, nawet parking na wózki.
Super!!!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: 非常喜歡這裡的自在感，像自家一樣輕鬆休閒，無論大人小孩都愛的地方，從小紮根的文化素養，沒有補習班的國度～大多設備均使用免費，僅需線上預約

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Das Gebäude selbst ist architektonisch sehr interessant. Man kann hier nicht nur Bücher und Magazine leihen, sondern auch z.B. Musikinstrumente. Es gibt ein gemütliches Café mit Außenterrasse. Auf jeden Fall einen Besuch wert.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Tappa fondamentale per chi visita Helsinki. Oltre ad essere bellissima, ogni spazio è perfettamente funzionale. Silenziosa negli spazi appositi, accogliente nella zona caffè, divertente nella zona bambini!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Honestamente, la mejor biblioteca que el ser humano ha podido visitar! La definición de profesionalidad, gran variedad de dispositivos electrónicos, sala de juegos de consolas y ordenadores, impresoras 3D, sala de recreativas, Wi-Fi 5G gratis, y lo mejor de todo, entrada ¡GRATIS!
La biblioteca muy amplia, con libros populares y de todas las épocas, con salas de silencio, de estudio, etc... Súper recomendada su visita. Como consecuencia incluye una sala de juegos para los pequeños y sala de ajedrez para garantizar las risas con la familia, y por último un mapa y una cafetería al lado de la entrada.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Fantastisk plats! En verklig mötesplats som fungerar i praktiken. Här har Sverige mycket att lära. Biblioteket är underbart vackert. Förutom det så finns det bland annat en terass för konserter och fika, biograf, en hel våning för kreativt arbete med datorer, instrument, 3D-printer, textilverkstad (att låna) med mera. Ode är en plats där människor verkligen möts och hänger. Jag blev verkligen glad över att upptäcka detta ställe 🤍

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Incuriosinata dalla quantità di persone che entravano in questo edificio ho seguito la massa. E che sorpresa, è la biblioteca pubblica, è una meraviglia e si trova a poca distanza dalla stazione centrale. Si sviluppa su più livelli. Si trovano dai tavolini per giocare a scacchi, laboratori, studi di registrazione, reciclaggio, tantissimi libri suddivisi in diverse categorie, divani, sedie e poltroncine di ogni tipo dove poter sedersi e rilassarsi il momento, un'area dedicata ai bambini, punti ristoro e persino il robottino che recupera i libri. Un luogo di cultura e comunità.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Visita obligada si esteu a Hèlsinki, amb i sense nens disfrutaré d'aquest espai cultural interactiu, trobareu biblioteca amb llibres fins taller de costura o impressió 3D.
Per rematar-ho, restaurant a la planta baixa self-service per només 13€ amb producte de qualitat.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
芬蘭🇫🇮赫爾辛基頌歌中央圖書館-Oodi Helsinki Central Library，流線感閱讀天堂！北歐絕美圖書館 ！

圖書館主建築體呈現船形，以玻璃、鋼鐵為骨架，並在建築表面附以大面積芬蘭雲杉木材，外型簡約而不失溫暖。共規劃三個樓層，每層依據芬蘭的教育思維規劃不同區域功能。一樓主要為展演與休憩空間，更有一座電影院與咖啡廳設置其中；二樓主要是中央圖書館相關工作人員的辦公、研究空間，規劃多媒體室、會議是與生活實驗室Living Lab；三樓則作為主要閱讀空間。

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: ほんまに図書館？本屋さんやんなぁ？綺麗やけど、静かに調べ物や勉強をするイメージの図書館とはかけ離れてる。この国が好きなジェンダーフリーの男子女子関係無いお手洗いも斬新的。子供も自由に暴れても騒いでも怒られない託児室のフリースペースみたいなパラダイス。フィンランドの人はザワザワした雰囲気の環境で本を読んだり勉強するのが好きなんかなぁ？図書館の域を超えたフィンランドらしいコンセプト。

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Bardzo duży obiekt z biblioteką,salami konferencyjnymi,miejscami do odpoczynku i zabaw dla dzieci .W obiekcie znajduje się również restauracja gdzie można się posilić i spotkać ze znajomymi ,również na ostatnim piętrze jest umieszczona kafejka.Na górze znajduje się taras widokowy gdzie bardzo dobrze widać parlament fiński.Wspaniałe miejsce do odwiedzenia z dziećmi.Polecam.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Magnífica biblioteca, con muchos detalles para los ciudadanos, desde los pequeños a los mayores , con oportunidades de usae tecnologías como impresoras 3d, estudios de grabación, videojuegos, salas de reuniones, ordenadores... Es impresionante y totalmente recomendable visitarla.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Diversa delle solite biblioteche, un'agorà dove vivere e fare esperienze, come giocare a scacchi, cucire, stampare file in 3D, giocare a videogiochi, una sala d'incisione musicale e tanto altro...

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
非常新穎的設計，絕對要去參觀！
免費入場，有露台、閱讀區、用餐區、電動區及做報告區
還有3d列印機

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Una bella biblioteca con gli scacchi all'entrata, zona bambini, lettura, sedie a dondolo, piccolo anfiteatro, terrazza con poltroncine e molto di più.
Per il benessere psico-fisico di tutti.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Una struttura per la comunità, pazzesca.
Ti fa comprendere l'educazione e il senso civico dei Finlandesi.
Veramente molto bella anche nell'architettura. Tantissime attività presenti all'interno.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
地點：市中心，搭車或走路都能到達。

建築外觀非常讓人印象深刻，美麗的木頭搭建和完美的弧度造型，第一次看到這麼漂亮的圖書館！值得前往參觀的當地圖書館！
可自由進出參觀。

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
今まで訪れた中でも最高の図書館。どこにいてもくつろげて、どこにいても居心地がいい。大階段の日の当たるクッションの上でいつまでも寝転がれるし、ガラス張りの窓に面したチェアでいつまでもぼーっとできます。

カフェに行くよりも、この図書館に来た方が、きっとのんびり過ごせます。

建築もユニークでとても面白いです。スタイリッシュなのに有機的。大胆なデザインだけれども、奇抜じゃなくて心地いいのが不思議です。

福祉国家の本気に恐れ入りました。

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Très belle bibliothèque avec énormément de coins de travail tous bien aménagés. Un rooftop accueille les visiteurs ou les étudiants en pause avec des jeux de société

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Excelente. Quando descobri este espaço maravilhoso, entendi que este país é realmente único, com um pensamento fora da caixa. Os livros estão misturados com todo o mundo contemporâneo, desde jogos digitais, analógicos, workshops onde se pode usar maquinas de costura, impressões 3D, robótica, parques para crianças usarem enquanto pegam num livro, correm descalços pelo espaço, tem recantos para todo o tipo de pessoas e necessidades sempre incentivando a criatividade, a socialização, a relação em comunidade, no meio de livros.. uau!

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Biblioteca moderna y espectacular en su interior que merece la pena la visita. Zona de niños, de estudio, de trabajo, de juego. Mucha luz natural

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Потрясное место для работы, отдыха, хобби, времени с семьёй и друзьями!
Есть детская зона, кафе, рабочая, отдельные комнаты, компьютеры, библиотека с лабиринтами книжных полок.....а также станок по печати больших фото, мастерская по вырезанию из дерева и швейные машинки!!
Восторг!! Рекомендую придти просто здорово время провести в окружении современных технологий и разумного благоустройства.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Oodin arkkitehtuuri leijailee, aaltoilee ja soi kevyenä, mutta sen sisältö on konkreettinen ja painava. Alakerran työpajat ja kerhot aukeavat yläkerran ilmavaan kirjastosaliin. Ihmisiä on vauvasta vaariin ja ilmapiiri on avoin ja arvostava.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Es la Biblioteca Central de Helsinki. Un edificio con una arquitectura moderna y que impresiona. Su interior muy cuidado, limpio, amplio, con vistas increíbles al exterior en todas sus alturas. Desde su terraza se pueden contemplar magníficas vistas a la plaza y al Parlamento. Es un lugar luminoso, con multitud de servicios, el personal es amable. Dispone de restaurante y cafetería. El café lo preparan con mimo y está delicioso. En la planta superior en la sala de estudio hay un montón de opciones para poder estudiar, butacas, sillas, pufs. La temperatura es agradable. Es un buen lugar donde concentrarse e inspirarse.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Architecture fabuleuse, entrée gratuite, allez au 3 ème étage pour une petite vue sur le quartier

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text:
Kyllä hieno paikka tämä keskuskirjasto.
Täällä voi tehdä melkein mitä tahansa.  On ompelukoneita, tulostimia, erilaisia työskentely- , kokous- ja opiskelutiloja, oleskelutiloja, lukusaleja, kahviloita ja ravintola. Täällä saa kulumaan helposti päivän kun on sopivaa tekemistä keksitty olosuhteet sen mahdollistavat. Ei ihme että ulkomaalaiset käyvät paikkaa katsomassa.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Великолепно. Книги на разных языках, настольные игры, 2 кафе, много места для отдыха

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: I Finlandesi sono avanti anni luce quando si parla di servizi! Una biblioteca dove al piano terra ci sono tavoli predisposti per il gioco degli scacchi, bar e ristorante. Il silenzio naturale dell'ambiente rende tutto estremamente rilassante. Al primo piano sale da gioco (playstation ecc...) sale riunioni, sale di registrazione e montaggio video, plotter, postazioni pc, stampanti 3D, taglio laser, macchine da cucire e tanto altro! Veramente un posto che in Italia ci sogniamo. Al secondo piano la biblioteca vera e propria dove poter leggere e cercare libri. Un robot aiuta gli addetti con i libri. Sedie girevoli alle vetrate regalano una vista della città dall'alto spettacolare. Bar con terrazzo e una zona completamente dedicata alle famiglie con tavolini per bambini (anche piccoli), postazioni per i passeggini e area gioco/lettura dedicata. La cosa fantastica è sempre il sereno silenzio che regna ovunque, un silenzio non imposto ma rispettoso è naturale. Un gioiellino che ognuno vorrebbe avere nella propria città.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Kitap az ama aslında etkinlik alanı gibi bir yer.

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Một địa điểm lý tưởng để cho mọi người sáng tạo thư giãn và và có nhiều ý tưởng mới

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
review_text: Отличное место с бесплатным вай фай, подходит для работы или групповых проектов , есть детские площадки, детские стульчики , комната матери и ребенка, детские книги на уровне детей, что очень удобно

name: Helsinki Central Library Oodi
